text.tspan: Under-5 mortality rate vs. GDP per capita, 2016
The share of children who die before reaching the age of 5. GDP per capita is adjusted for inflation and differences in
the cost of living between countries.
Source: Gapminder (v10); Maddison Project Database 2020 (Bolt and van Zanden (2020))
Note: GDP per capita is expressed in international-$ at 2011 prices.
